' Description: Split a record containing multiple photographs into multiple records containing one photograph.
If Editing Then Halt "Please save the record first"
Set flds=ActiveRecord.Fields
Set imgs=ActiveRecord.Images
nPictures=imgs.Count
If nPictures=0 Then Halt
StatusRange=nPictures
For i=1 to nPictures-1
 picno=Right(100+i+1,2) ' two-digit number with a leading zero.
 Set rec=Database.NewRecord
 Set fldsNew=rec.Fields
 flds.TextFormat=cbxTextIndex
 fldsNew.TextFormat=cbxTextIndex
 For Each fld In flds
  if fld.Definition.Type=cbxFieldTypeText then fldsNew(fld.Name)=fld.Text
  Next
 rec.Images.Add imgs(i+1)
 fldsNew("number")=fldsNew("number") & "." & picno
 rec.Save
 Records.Add rec
 StatusPosition=i
 Next
Set rec=ActiveRecord
 rec.Edit
 nPictures=rec.Images.Count
 for i=2 to nPictures
  rec.Images.Remove i
  Next 
 rec.Fields("number")=rec.Fields("number") & ".01"
 rec.Save
